Source: fi
Priority: extra
Section: libdevel
Maintainer: Alexandre Raymond <alexandre.j.raymond@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/gsarkis/libfi
Vcs-Git: git://github.com/ajraymond/libfi-debian.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/ajraymond/libfi-debian
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 8.0.0), doxygen, dpkg-dev (>= 1.16.1~), graphviz
Standards-Version: 3.9.4

Package: libfi-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: C++ fixed-point arithmetic library
 Libfi is a header-only C++ library allowing application developers
 to easily make use of fixed-point arithmetic in their applications.
 This library overrides many common C++ operators for
 plug-and-play operation.
 .
 The behavior of this library with respect to saturation and 
 overflow is fully parameterizable at compile time.
 .
 This library consists only of header files to be included in the
 target applications; it is not pre-compiled nor dynamically
 linked.

Package: libfi-doc
Architecture: all
Section: doc
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Documentation for the libfi C++ fixed point library
 Libfi is a header-only fixed-point arithmetic library for C++.
 .
 This package contains  documentation for the library in HTML format,
 automatically generated using Doxygen.
